      <h2>Fact-checking</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.snopes.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Snopes</a></strong> — The internet's oldest fact-checking site. Covers religious claims, urban legends, and misinformation.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.politifact.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">PolitiFact</a></strong> — Fact-checking political claims, including those involving religion in public policy.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://skepticalscience.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Skeptical Science</a></strong> — Evidence-based responses to climate change denial.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Logical fallacies & biases</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="https://yourlogicalfallacyis.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Your Logical Fallacy Is</a></strong> — Beautifully designed fallacy reference with examples.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://yourbias.is" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Your Bias Is</a></strong> — Cognitive bias reference companion.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.txstate.edu/philosophy/resources/fallacy-definitions.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Texas State Fallacy Definitions</a></strong> — Academic definitions with formal and informal fallacy categories.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Counter-apologetics</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.ironchariots.wiki" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Iron Chariots</a></strong> — Wiki covering arguments for and against the existence of God.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://infidels.org/library/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Internet Infidels Library</a></strong> — Extensive essay library on atheism, naturalism, and secular ethics.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.skepticsannotatedbible.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Skeptic's Annotated Bible</a></strong> — The Bible with annotations highlighting contradictions, absurdities, and cruelties.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Podcasts</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="https://ffrf.org/news/radio" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Freethought Radio</a></strong> — Weekly from the Freedom From Religion Foundation.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.atheist-experience.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">The Atheist Experience</a></strong> — Live call-in show discussing atheism and theism.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.pointofinquiry.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Point of Inquiry</a></strong> — CFI's podcast on science, secularism, and society.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.youarenotaloneshow.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">You Are Not Alone</a></strong> — Stories of leaving religion and finding community.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Publications</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="https://secularhumanism.org/free-inquiry/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Free Inquiry</a></strong> — Bimonthly magazine of secular humanism.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://skepticalinquirer.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Skeptical Inquirer</a></strong> — Magazine for science and reason.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://thehumanist.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">The Humanist</a></strong> — Published since 1941 by the American Humanist Association.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://newhumanist.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">New Humanist</a></strong> — UK-based magazine on ideas and culture.</li>
      </ul>

